@node Intro "Midnight AmigaGuide User Manual"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~

  TITLE

    Midnight - Modular screen/mouse blanking system

  VERSION

    Version 2 Revision 08

  AUTHOR

    Trevor N. Andrews

  DESCRIPTION

    Midnight is a modular screen blanking system designed
    with AmigaDOS 2.x/3.x in mind.  A few of its features
    are listed below:

    Ę Screen Mode selection in all modules with AGA support
    Ę Standard 2.x Preferences interface
    Ę Font sensitive window
    Ę Enforcer/Mungwall Proof Code
    Ę Public screen support
    Ę GadTools interface
    Ę IFF Preference file
    Ę Separate Dameon and GUI
    Ę Amiga Guide support (library is optional)
    Ę NT/PT music support in every module!

    Currently, the following blanker modules are available:

    Ę ALock          (Full featured security system)
    Ę Nightfall      (Simple black screen)
    Ę Rainbow        (Bouncing lines with 256 colours in AGA)
    Ę Shuffle        (Slides selectable pieces around)
    Ę Mindmelt      *(An AfterDark inspired module)
    Ę PhaseFade      (Fade to black)
    Ę Fireworks      (Traditional fireworks with 256 colours in AGA)
    Ę Textual        (Floats text around)
    Ę Spotlight      (Your screen has just broke out of jail)
    Ę IceMelt       *(Screen melts like an ice cube)
    Ę Starfield      (Prepare for space flight)
    Ę Random         (Randomly chooses your modules)
    Ę Breadth        (It's strange...)
    Ę Worms          (They crawl in and they crawl out!)
    Ę Aquarium       ("Under the sea", are you singing along?)
    Ę FlyingToilets  (Those flying creatures are up to trouble again)

      * Not included in this release.

    Additional features include:

    Ę Concise message signaling system
    Ę OS friendly mouse blanker
    Ę Support for detection of gameport 
    Ę Random blanker selection mode

@endnode


